# UI/UX Direction

Read `.impeccable.md` before making visual changes.

This is the real project: `/Users/bhavyakaushal/dev/neighbours-cafe/WEB`.

Design as a senior UI/UX designer and frontend engineer. Keep the existing Next.js app structure and improve the product quality in place.

## Must Keep

- Local assets from `public/assets/cafe`.
- Full-bleed, image-led homepage composition.
- Warm St Kilda East cafe tone: brunch, courtyard, dogs, street art.
- Existing route pages: `/`, `/menu`, `/dog-menu`, `/find-us`, `/about`.
- Framer Motion/GSAP/Lenis stack if motion is needed.

## Improve Toward

- Stronger first-viewport brand signal.
- More intentional hero text placement and image readability.
- Clear, useful CTAs for menu, dog menu, directions, and story.
- Better section rhythm, spacing, and mobile typography.
- Subtle graffiti/artwork integration through backgrounds, seams, dividers, and hover details.

## Avoid

- Remote stock images.
- Generic cafe templates.
- Fake graffiti graphics.
- Overbuilt card grids.
- Text over busy image areas.
- In-app explanations of design choices.
